    <note>Guo(1) Quan [942] His ancestors moved from Taiyuan jun, Yangqu xian to Dongping, Xucheng xian. Yuanming's [3458] father and Maoxun's [953] grandfather. Maoxun's mother and Yuanming's wife was Li(2) Yingji's [1120] granddaughter. Yuanming was the father-in-law of Su(1) Song's [8116] son, Xi(a) [3757], and of Sun(1) Yaqing [3786], who had the same generational name as Sun(1) Yafu [1549]. Quan was appointed Zizhou yunpan in 6/.5/1029 when the office was first established, but he never assumed the post, which was later assigned to Xu Yue. XCB, 118.6a, 148.9a; SHY:ZG, 64.44b-45b; SHY:SH, 49.12b; SS, 297.10a-12a; Su Song, WJ, 59.9b; Du Dagui, 'zhong, ' 30.4b. CBD, 3, 2129.</note>
